<strong>The apiary scoop</strong>

A long wooden scoop for lifting combs and wax out of a living <a href="apiary">hive</a> without enraging it. The <strong>only</strong> way to harvest an apiary.

<strong>Recipe</strong>
One plank atop two sticks, stacked in a column. Cheap by design.

<strong>Durability</strong>
96. Each harvest costs one point, so one scoop is good for roughly 96 harvests of weekly rounds.

<strong>Why bare hands fail</strong>
You cannot work a living hive without the right tool. Reach in empty-handed — or with anything else — and the hive refuses you. The colony is tamed, so nothing stings; the combs simply stay where they are until the scoop arrives.
